708799f-a.title: Manhattan: 5th Avenue - 43rd Street
708799f-a.text:
Fifth Avenue, east side, from East 43rd (right) to 45th
(left) Street's, showing prominently the Temple Emanu El.
This is at the N. E. corner of 43rd Street, and was erected
in 1868. It will be demolished in 1927 and replaced with
the office structure, the Lefcourt-National Building.
The fenced plot on the right (S. E. corner of 43rd St.)
was the site of the former ''Boss'' Tweed home. The Postal
LLife Insurance Co. Hldg. was erected there later.
About 1890
Thru the New York Historical Society
